    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing the author's intent within the canonical and historical context of ancient Israel and the trajectory toward the New Testament. The movements below follow the chapter's own argument: centralized worship, the anti-demonic statute, the blood prohibition, and the atonement-theology of verse 11 that explains all the rest. Where the Hebrew sharpens the English, a brief note supplements the exposition.",
